WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:02.710
Hey, good morning family. Praise the

00:00:02.720 --> 00:00:04.710
Lord and welcome to our broadcast. Well,

00:00:04.720 --> 00:00:07.030
it's Diana and Brandon and we're excited

00:00:07.040 --> 00:00:08.549
to be here. We have some things on our

00:00:08.559 --> 00:00:10.870
heart. There's a lot going on, and I

00:00:10.880 --> 00:00:13.350
say that every time. But my goodness,

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:15.669
we laugh about it because

00:00:15.679 --> 00:00:17.430
of all the things that are happening

00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:19.830
right now. It seems like every time you

00:00:19.840 --> 00:00:21.269
turn around, there's something

00:00:21.279 --> 00:00:24.870
new going on. I mean,

00:00:24.880 --> 00:00:28.470
the IRS

00:00:28.470 --> 00:00:28.480
is

00:00:28.480 --> 00:00:30.310
getting rid of 20,000 people. Then we

00:00:30.320 --> 00:00:33.030
had the main IRS guy say he's

00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:35.270
quitting. That's a big deal in America.

00:00:35.280 --> 00:00:36.549
I don't know, that might not

00:00:36.559 --> 00:00:39.030
be a big deal to other nations right

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:40.630
now because I know I'm talking to

00:00:40.640 --> 00:00:42.869
everybody, but here,

00:00:42.879 --> 00:00:45.910
it's like a circus on the news. What

00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:49.190
is going on? The stock

00:00:49.200 --> 00:00:51.750
market is still kind of teeter-tottery, but

00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:53.910
God's still on the throne.

00:00:53.920 --> 00:00:55.910
He's not falling off and the

00:00:55.920 --> 00:00:58.549
sky is not falling. All we know is that

00:00:58.559 --> 00:01:01.349
Jesus is coming and he's coming soon.

00:01:01.359 --> 00:01:03.270
But I have a word of encouragement for

00:01:03.280 --> 00:01:06.469
y'all today. One of my favorite

00:01:06.479 --> 00:01:09.550
passages in the Bible is Genesis

00:01:09.560 --> 00:01:13.350
26. There was famine in the land. And I

00:01:13.360 --> 00:01:16.550
know that God told me—I feel

00:01:16.560 --> 00:01:19.270
in my spirit—'Brandon, I'm

00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:20.630
going to give you a window of

00:01:20.640 --> 00:01:23.429
opportunity before a major shaking takes

00:01:23.439 --> 00:01:26.469
place, a major opportunity for the body

00:01:26.479 --> 00:01:28.469
of Christ, the ones that are

00:01:28.469 --> 00:01:28.479
listening.'And

00:01:28.479 --> 00:01:29.749
I'm praying for that

00:01:29.759 --> 00:01:32.149
opportunity. Show us, Lord, what it is

00:01:32.159 --> 00:01:34.149
for the windows to open up over our

00:01:34.159 --> 00:01:35.990
household because I know what

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:38.630
he's called us to do. And we cannot do

00:01:38.640 --> 00:01:41.510
it in the natural without a surplus.

00:01:41.520 --> 00:01:43.350
It's going to take the fishes and the

00:01:43.360 --> 00:01:45.670
loaves type of a miracle for what God

00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:47.670
has called Diana and I to do in these

00:01:47.680 --> 00:01:49.830
last days. We talk about it

00:01:49.830 --> 00:01:49.840
and

00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:51.350
we pray about it. I know we haven't

00:01:51.360 --> 00:01:53.190
stepped fully into what he's told us to

00:01:53.200 --> 00:01:56.870
do, but you don't start at a

00:01:56.880 --> 00:01:59.270
run. You start to learn how to walk

00:01:59.280 --> 00:02:02.310
and jog first, right? Most people

00:02:02.320 --> 00:02:05.190
try to run first. It's time

00:02:05.200 --> 00:02:07.350
to apply some wisdom with this. But I

00:02:07.360 --> 00:02:10.150
was thinking about

00:02:10.160 --> 00:02:12.390
the passage

00:02:12.390 --> 00:02:12.400
where

00:02:12.400 --> 00:02:14.949
there was famine in the land with Isaac,

00:02:14.959 --> 00:02:18.309
and he planted and he sowed in famine.

00:02:18.319 --> 00:02:20.470
Just read that, honey. I think it's

00:02:20.480 --> 00:02:23.270
just a blessing.

00:02:23.280 --> 00:02:24.710
You can read the first couple of

00:02:24.720 --> 00:02:26.949
verses up here and then let's go

00:02:26.959 --> 00:02:30.309
down to verse 12. 'And there was a

00:02:30.319 --> 00:02:32.630
famine in the land other than the former

00:02:32.640 --> 00:02:35.270
famine that was in the days of Abraham.

00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:38.150
And Isaac went to Gerar to

00:02:38.150 --> 00:02:38.160
Abimelech, king—I

00:02:38.160 --> 00:02:41.550
probably butchered

00:02:41.550 --> 00:02:41.560
that—Abimelech,

00:02:41.560 --> 00:02:43.869
king of the

00:02:43.879 --> 00:02:45.990
Philistines. And the Lord appeared to

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:48.869
him and said, "Do not go down to Egypt.

00:02:48.879 --> 00:02:50.710
Live in the land of which I will tell

00:02:50.720 --> 00:02:53.589
you, dwell temporarily in this land, and

00:02:53.599 --> 00:02:55.589
I will be with you and will favor you

00:02:55.599 --> 00:02:58.309
with blessings for you and to your

00:02:58.319 --> 00:03:01.030
descendants. I will give all these lands

00:03:01.040 --> 00:03:03.030
and I will perform the oath which I

00:03:03.040 --> 00:03:05.990
swore to Abraham your father and I will

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:07.190
make your descendants..."'So pause right

00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:09.430
there for a second.

00:03:09.440 --> 00:03:11.670
A key to walking in the blessing is

00:03:11.680 --> 00:03:14.710
obedience. Just right there: being

00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:17.270
where God has called you to be

00:03:17.280 --> 00:03:19.270
regardless of what you feel. Don't go

00:03:19.280 --> 00:03:20.869
down to Egypt because that's probably

00:03:20.879 --> 00:03:22.470
where the hot spot was. It's

00:03:22.480 --> 00:03:24.470
probably the major hub of all the

00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:26.390
finances back then. Egypt was

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:28.229
probably it, I'm sure.

00:03:28.239 --> 00:03:29.509
So everybody was like,

00:03:29.519 --> 00:03:31.430
'We got to go to Egypt because that's

00:03:31.440 --> 00:03:32.869
where the money's at.'But he says,

00:03:32.879 --> 00:03:34.949
'Stay where you are.'And there's a

00:03:34.959 --> 00:03:37.030
famine in the land. I'm sure Isaac was

00:03:37.040 --> 00:03:39.670
like, 'What? Seriously?'So he went down

00:03:39.680 --> 00:03:41.149
to the king

00:03:41.149 --> 00:03:41.159
Abimelech

00:03:41.159 --> 00:03:43.190
to the Philistines because he's

00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:44.630
like, 'We got to go try to make some

00:03:44.640 --> 00:03:47.509
trade deals or

00:03:47.509 --> 00:03:47.519
something.'But

00:03:47.519 --> 00:03:49.830
going all the way

00:03:49.830 --> 00:03:49.840
down—because

00:03:49.840 --> 00:03:52.509
this is a big

00:03:52.509 --> 00:03:52.519
chapter—read

00:03:52.519 --> 00:03:56.470
verse 12. That's my

00:03:56.480 --> 00:04:00.149
favorite. 'Then Isaac sowed seed in that

00:04:00.159 --> 00:04:02.229
land and received in the same year a

00:04:02.239 --> 00:04:04.550
hundred times as much as he had planted.

00:04:04.560 --> 00:04:08.390
And the Lord favored him with

00:04:08.390 --> 00:04:08.400
blessings.'I

00:04:08.400 --> 00:04:11.589
just thought if God did it for him, he'll do it

00:04:11.599 --> 00:04:14.949
every single time. But he had

00:04:14.959 --> 00:04:17.749
to do something. He had to sow the seed.

00:04:17.759 --> 00:04:19.349
He didn't just sit back and wait for God

00:04:19.359 --> 00:04:21.749
to do it; he didn't just

00:04:21.759 --> 00:04:22.430
say,

00:04:22.440 --> 00:04:25.590
'God, make it happen.'He

00:04:25.590 --> 00:04:25.600
sowed

00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:29.830
the seed. And

00:04:29.840 --> 00:04:31.430
just like we do, we sow into the

00:04:31.440 --> 00:04:33.830
offerings. We sow into the church. We

00:04:33.830 --> 00:04:33.840
sow

00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:37.189
into God's work. In

00:04:37.189 --> 00:04:37.199
that sowing

00:04:37.199 --> 00:04:40.710
into what God has called you to do by

00:04:40.720 --> 00:04:42.070
being obedient to the word whenever he

00:04:42.080 --> 00:04:43.990
tells you to do it, he obeyed him. He

00:04:43.990 --> 00:04:44.000
sowed

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:45.510
and he stayed in the land where he

00:04:45.510 --> 00:04:45.520
was

00:04:45.520 --> 00:04:47.670
supposed to be. And he

00:04:47.670 --> 00:04:47.680
sowed

00:04:47.680 --> 00:04:51.270
in famine whenever we see

00:04:51.280 --> 00:04:53.110
what's going on on the news right now.

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:54.870
The sky is falling, Chicken Little. I

00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:57.670
mean, it's like trade wars.

00:04:57.680 --> 00:04:59.510
Oh no, China's done

00:04:59.520 --> 00:05:01.590
something else—stopping the

00:05:01.600 --> 00:05:03.749
minerals and the magnets. My

00:05:03.759 --> 00:05:06.390
goodness, it looks like a

00:05:06.400 --> 00:05:08.310
famine's trying to come on. It looks

00:05:08.320 --> 00:05:11.029
like what I hear is that

00:05:11.039 --> 00:05:13.590
Warren Buffett has all this and what

00:05:13.600 --> 00:05:15.270
they're doing. I get all these

00:05:15.280 --> 00:05:16.590
articles and it

00:05:16.590 --> 00:05:16.600
causes

00:05:16.600 --> 00:05:19.510
your flesh to shake a

00:05:19.520 --> 00:05:21.189
little bit. Like I told you, if you're

00:05:21.199 --> 00:05:22.189
going

00:05:22.199 --> 00:05:24.310
horizontal, looking at everything right

00:05:24.320 --> 00:05:26.550
now

00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:29.270
in the natural, it makes you go,

00:05:29.280 --> 00:05:31.510
'Whoa, a little shaky.'I'm like, 'Hold

00:05:31.520 --> 00:05:33.110
on a

00:05:33.110 --> 00:05:33.120
minute.'For

00:05:33.120 --> 00:05:34.629
what the Lord has blessed us

00:05:34.639 --> 00:05:36.950
with, you go, 'Should we bury

00:05:40.629 --> 00:05:40.639
it?'You

00:05:44.240 --> 00:05:46.390
start thinking in the natural. But you

00:05:46.400 --> 00:05:47.749
have to think in the spiritual because

00:05:47.759 --> 00:05:49.990
I'm going to tell you: sowing in famine

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:52.790
sounds really dumb.

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:55.670
Why would you sow any seed when there's

00:05:55.680 --> 00:05:59.909
no rain? There's drought; it's famine.

00:05:59.919 --> 00:06:03.430
But he obeyed God. He sowed in famine

00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:05.350
and he reaped. Read it again. What

00:06:05.360 --> 00:06:08.469
happened? 'Then Isaac sowed seed in that

00:06:08.479 --> 00:06:11.270
land and received in the same year a

00:06:11.280 --> 00:06:13.510
hundred times as much as he had planted.

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:15.590
And the Lord favored him with blessings.

00:06:15.600 --> 00:06:17.830
And the man became great and gained more

00:06:17.840 --> 00:06:20.150
and more until he became very wealthy

00:06:20.160 --> 00:06:22.790
and distinguished. He owned flocks,

00:06:22.800 --> 00:06:26.550
herds, and a great supply of servants.

00:06:26.560 --> 00:06:29.670
And the Philistines envied him.'Now, why would they envy him? Because it didn't happen to the unjust. They were jealous because their crops didn't turn around and reap a hundredfold. They were going, 'What gives?'and looking at him going, 'He's walking in the blessing and the favor of God's all over him.'And he's doing exactly what God had called him to do in the famine. The blessing and the favor of the Lord was on him in a supernatural way. Now, ladies and gentlemen, if God would do that for Isaac in famine, how much more will he do it for you? How much more will God bless your hands and whatever you put your hands to will it prosper if you just believe him? If you put your boat into motion and not sit idly by and go, 'Well, where's my angel with the money sack?'Isaac planted in famine. But you have to be—bottom line—you have to be where God has called you to be. You have to be doing what God has called you to do. And if you are and you're in that place of obedience, blessing is behind the obedience. So keep going, baby. You can keep reading. 'Now all

00:06:29.680 --> 00:06:32.150
the wells which his father's servants

00:06:32.160 --> 00:06:34.469
had dug

00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:48.629
in the days of Abraham

00:07:48.639 --> 00:07:51.029
his father, the Philistines had closed

00:07:51.039 --> 00:07:53.189
and filled with earth.'And that's

00:07:53.199 --> 00:07:55.189
jealousy right there. They're going

00:07:55.199 --> 00:07:56.629
to fill all those wells up. 'We don't

00:07:56.639 --> 00:07:57.830
want you blessed, so we're going to fill

00:07:57.840 --> 00:07:59.909
your well

00:07:59.909 --> 00:07:59.919
up.'There's

00:07:59.919 --> 00:08:02.070
always going to be somebody

00:08:02.080 --> 00:08:03.749
trying to fill your well up, trying to

00:08:03.759 --> 00:08:06.790
put dirt on your well

00:08:06.800 --> 00:08:08.390
coming out of you. 'Oh, that can't

00:08:08.400 --> 00:08:10.629
happen. You'll never make it.'Those are

00:08:10.639 --> 00:08:12.469
the well cover-uppers here.

00:08:12.479 --> 00:08:14.629
We don't have actual wells that they try

00:08:14.639 --> 00:08:16.790
to block, but there's always somebody

00:08:16.800 --> 00:08:18.629
trying to speak doubt into your

00:08:18.639 --> 00:08:20.629
faith, telling you you can't do

00:08:20.639 --> 00:08:23.350
what God's told you you can do. And

00:08:23.360 --> 00:08:25.390
don't you know there's famine out there,

00:08:25.400 --> 00:08:28.950
dummy? But you have

00:08:28.960 --> 00:08:31.189
your eyes on God. You're going vertical.

00:08:32.519 --> 00:08:34.949
They filled the wells up.

00:08:34.959 --> 00:08:37.190
Sorry for interjecting what

00:08:37.200 --> 00:08:40.790
the Lord said. Abimelech said to Isaac,

00:08:40.800 --> 00:08:43.589
'Go away from us, for you are much

00:08:43.599 --> 00:08:46.150
mightier than we are.'So Isaac went

00:08:46.160 --> 00:08:47.990
away from there and pitched his tent in

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:50.389
the valley of Gerar and dwelt there.

00:08:50.399 --> 00:08:52.630
And Isaac dug again the wells of water

00:08:52.640 --> 00:08:54.070
which had been dug in the days of

00:08:54.080 --> 00:08:56.070
Abraham his father, for the Philistines

00:08:56.080 --> 00:08:57.829
had stopped them after the death of

00:08:57.839 --> 00:09:00.070
Abraham. And he gave them the names by

00:09:00.080 --> 00:09:02.070
which his father had called them. Now

00:09:02.080 --> 00:09:04.070
Isaac's servants dug in the valley and

00:09:04.080 --> 00:09:05.670
found there a well of living spring

00:09:05.680 --> 00:09:07.269
water. And the

00:09:07.279 --> 00:09:10.230
herdsmen of

00:09:10.230 --> 00:09:10.240
Gerar

00:09:10.240 --> 00:09:12.389
quarreled with Isaac's herdsmen, saying,

00:09:12.399 --> 00:09:14.550
'The water is ours.'And he named the

00:09:14.560 --> 00:09:16.949
well Esek, meaning contention, because they

00:09:16.949 --> 00:09:16.959
quarreled

00:09:16.959 --> 00:09:19.670
with him. Then his servants dug

00:09:19.680 --> 00:09:21.190
another well and they quarreled over that

00:09:21.200 --> 00:09:24.470
also. So he named it Sitnah,

00:09:24.470 --> 00:09:24.480
meaning enmity.

00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:26.550
And he moved away from there

00:09:26.560 --> 00:09:29.190
and dug another well; for that one they

00:09:29.200 --> 00:09:32.230
did not quarrel. He named it Rehoboth,

00:09:32.230 --> 00:09:32.240
meaning

00:09:32.240 --> 00:09:34.630
room, saying, 'For now the Lord has made

00:09:34.640 --> 00:09:37.030
room for us and we will be fruitful in

00:09:37.040 --> 00:09:39.110
the

00:09:39.110 --> 00:09:39.120
land.'Yeah,

00:09:39.120 --> 00:09:40.310
but there are always going to be

00:09:40.320 --> 00:09:42.230
people trying to leech off

00:09:42.240 --> 00:09:44.550
your blessing too. But there's so much

00:09:44.560 --> 00:09:46.710
abundance on you that it won't matter.

00:09:46.720 --> 00:09:49.829
Now he went up from there to

00:09:49.829 --> 00:09:49.839
Beersheba,

00:09:49.839 --> 00:09:51.590
and the Lord appeared to him that same

00:09:51.600 --> 00:09:53.990
night and said, 'I am the God of Abraham

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:56.550
your father. Fear not, for I am with

00:09:56.560 --> 00:09:58.790
you, and I will favor you with blessings

00:09:58.800 --> 00:10:00.790
and multiply your descendants for the

00:10:00.800 --> 00:10:03.590
sake of my servant Abraham.'And Isaac

00:10:03.600 --> 00:10:05.350
built an altar there and called on the

00:10:05.360 --> 00:10:06.870
name of the Lord and pitched his tent

00:10:06.880 --> 00:10:09.110
there. And there Isaac's servants were

00:10:09.120 --> 00:10:12.509
digging a well. Basically, a well is

00:10:12.519 --> 00:10:15.750
life. Even in our time right now,

00:10:15.760 --> 00:10:18.870
a well brings forth life; it brings forth

00:10:18.870 --> 00:10:18.880
greenery.

00:10:18.880 --> 00:10:21.110
Because if you

00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:23.269
don't have the fresh living water of

00:10:23.279 --> 00:10:25.110
the word coming up out of you, you're

00:10:25.120 --> 00:10:27.590
dry. So even then, it's a type

00:10:27.590 --> 00:10:27.600
and

00:10:27.600 --> 00:10:30.389
shadow. We've got to get in that river,

00:10:30.399 --> 00:10:33.110
that well coming up out of us, and

00:10:33.120 --> 00:10:35.590
have that going on in these last days in

00:10:35.600 --> 00:10:37.350
the time of famine. There's a word

00:10:37.360 --> 00:10:40.389
famine going on too. If you

00:10:40.399 --> 00:10:42.630
haven't noticed, there seems to be a

00:10:42.640 --> 00:10:46.150
word famine. And we see that Isaac

00:10:46.160 --> 00:10:50.990
was determined to keep the

00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:55.030
wells open because he knew where

00:10:55.040 --> 00:10:57.750
the life came from. He knew how much he

00:10:57.760 --> 00:10:59.750
had to have that living well. How much

00:10:59.760 --> 00:11:01.430
more do we need that living well

00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:05.509
coming up out of us and having

00:11:05.519 --> 00:11:07.750
this freshness of this new fire? It

00:11:07.750 --> 00:11:07.760
sounds

00:11:07.760 --> 00:11:10.150
like the Lord

00:11:10.160 --> 00:11:12.389
himself appeared. It says the Lord

00:11:12.399 --> 00:11:15.870
appeared to him in the Old Covenant,

00:11:15.880 --> 00:11:18.310
y'all. This isn't

00:11:18.320 --> 00:11:20.870
New Covenant. How many of y'all

00:11:20.880 --> 00:11:24.150
know that Jesus will appear to you

00:11:24.150 --> 00:11:24.160
and

00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:26.470
will have a relationship with you? But

00:11:26.480 --> 00:11:28.150
you think, 'Well, it's just for Brandon;

00:11:28.160 --> 00:11:29.990
it's just for Diana. The Lord just

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:32.190
appears to them; He won't talk to

00:11:32.190 --> 00:11:32.200
me.'He's

00:11:32.200 --> 00:11:35.030
no respecter of

00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:38.630
persons. And I want to tell you all,

00:11:38.630 --> 00:11:38.640
from

00:11:38.640 --> 00:11:40.430
what I have seen

00:11:40.440 --> 00:11:43.670
coming, you better get Genesis 26 down

00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:46.710
inside of you, understanding that

00:11:46.720 --> 00:11:49.350
we can sow in famine. And not only can

00:11:49.360 --> 00:11:52.470
we sow in famine, but we can reap a

